Genre: 2D Pixel-Art Narrative Co-op Adventure
 Engine: Godot (Offline Co-op)
 Players: 2 (Human / Ghost)
 Theme: Connection between life and death; fleeting cooperation; light versus shadow

Premise

Every midnight, a forgotten subway beneath the city becomes a passageway between worlds.
One traveler is alive — a commuter trapped underground. 
The other is a wandering ghost, bound to the tunnels since the accident that took her life.
During that short time, they must work together to find the way out — or be lost to the rails forever.
Human is sorta a lost soul, not knowing why they're in the metro station in the first place,
but remembers a fleeting memory about his death as soon as he senses the ghost's presence. 

Gameplay Overview

Dual-World Exploration
 Each player sees a different version of the same map: the Human World (physical) and the Spirit World (ethereal).

Co-op Puzzles
 Progress requires both roles: the Human manipulates the boxes(physical things); The Ghost can see the where these boxes need to be placed.
 The Human needs to fetch the key to the door; The Ghost needs to guide the Human to the key because only the Ghost can see the maze; 

Player Roles

Human (The Commuter)
Controls physical obstacles.
Vulnerable to darkness; must rely on the Ghost’s guidance.


Ghost (The Wanderer)
Reveals hidden paths and positions. 
Needs the human help with physical obstacles. 


Structure and Progression

Level format:  Entrance -> Maze -> Station -> Exit
Each level’s puzzle revolves around the interplay of two realities (for example, Human repairs power while Ghost guides through a dark maze).



Art and Tone

Pixel art with modern lighting (URP 2D Lights, bloom, parallax).
Deep blues, greys, and violets with bursts of gold during merges.
Melancholy yet hopeful mood — a liminal mix of cyberpunk and ghost story.



PUZZLES:

Box Positioning: Human has to move 3 physical boxes to a certain position. Ghost can only see those highlighted position and has to guide the player. 
Patrolling Guard: Human has to navigate through a specific area of the metro to get the key to the door. Ghost will tell human which ways to go to reach the key. Takes place in a darker area. 


Game Concept — Afterlight Metro
